How to setup application

1. Install XAMPP/AMPPS on the new laptop

2. Open XAMPP/AMPPS Control Panel

3. Start Apache

4. Start MySQL

5. Unzip the project

6. Move the folder to "www" in AMPPS

7. Ensure the folder name is ClassRoom_Checkin

8. Open a browser

9. Go to http://localhost/ClassRoom_Checkin/install.php

10. Confirm you see setup Database connection error (database not ready yet)

11. Open http://localhost/phpmyadmin

12. Create a database named classroom_checkin

13. Import the schema.sql

14. Refresh http://localhost/ClassRoom_Checkin/install.php

15. Confirm you see “Database detected”

16. Go to http://localhost/ClassRoom_Checkin/login.php



Navigating the app


1. Register account as a student or instructor (ideally register in as instructor first)
(instructor)
Go to http://localhost/classroom-checkin/login.php

Enter instructor email

Enter instructor password

Click Login

You are redirected to the instructor dashboard

View assigned classes and session statistics

Navigate to Sessions

View all class sessions (date, time, location, status)

Activate or deactivate class sessions as needed

Confirm session location and radius

Navigate to Attendance Overview

Select a class session

View list of students checked in

Review check-in times and locations

Log out of the instructor account

Session ends and you are returned to the login page










(Student)
Go to http://localhost/classroom-checkin/login.php

Enter student email

Enter student password

Click Login

You are redirected to the student dashboard

Review your enrolled classes and available sessions

Navigate to the Check-In page

Select the correct class session

Allow browser location access when prompted

Click Verify Location

Wait for confirmation that you are within range

Click Check In

Receive confirmation message for successful check-in

Navigate to Attendance History

View past attendance records and timestamps

Click Logout

Session ends and you are returned to the login page
